The function in Microsoft SQL Server that returns the first non-NULL value from multiple columns is COALESCE.
Simple Definition (very easy words)
COALESCE() → returns the first value that is not NULL from a list of columns.
Think like this:
If the first value is empty, check the next one, then the next one, until a value is found.
Syntax
SQL
COALESCE(column1, column2, column3, ...)
It checks from left → right and returns the first non-NULL value.
Example Table
Student table
Id
Phone1
Phone2
Phone3
1
NULL
9876543210
NULL
2
NULL
NULL
8888888888
3
9999999999
8888888888
7777777777
Query
SQL
SELECT 
Id,
COALESCE(Phone1, Phone2, Phone3) AS ContactNumber
FROM Student;
Output
Id
ContactNumber
